name: Maasai Mara National Reserve
notes: Famous for the Great Migration and rich wildlife, including lions, elephants, and cheetahs.

name: Santorini
notes: Known for its stunning sunsets, white-washed buildings, and crystal-clear waters.

name: Diani Beach
notes: A beautiful white-sand beach with clear waters, perfect for snorkeling and diving.

name: Machu Picchu
notes: An ancient Incan city nestled in the Andes mountains, known for its archaeological significance.

name: Great Wall of China
notes: An ancient world wonder, stretching over 13,000 miles with breathtaking views.

name: Mount Kenya
notes: Africa's second-highest peak, offering scenic trekking routes and stunning views.

name: Sydney Opera House
notes: A world-renowned architectural marvel, located in the Sydney Harbour.

name: Amboseli National Park
notes: Known for its large elephant herds and breathtaking views of Mount Kilimanjaro.

name: Eiffel Tower
notes: An iconic symbol of Paris, offering stunning views of the city from its observation decks.

name: Lamu Island
notes: A UNESCO World Heritage Site with rich Swahili culture and historic architecture.

name: Grand Canyon
notes: A natural wonder, known for its immense size and colorful landscape carved by the Colorado River.

name: Taj Mahal
notes: A UNESCO World Heritage Site and symbol of love, known for its stunning white marble architecture.

name: Victoria Falls
notes: One of the largest and most famous waterfalls in the world, located on the Zambezi River.

name: Pyramids of Giza
notes: Ancient wonders of the world, located near Cairo, known for their historical significance and grandeur.

name: Banff National Park
notes: A beautiful national park in the Canadian Rockies, known for its stunning lakes, mountains, and wildlife.

name: Lake Nakuru National Park
notes: Famous for its flamingo population and diverse bird species in a beautiful lakeside setting.

name: Samburu National Reserve
notes: Home to unique wildlife species like the Grevy's zebra, reticulated giraffe, and Somali ostrich.

name: Hell's Gate National Park
notes: Offers hiking and rock climbing opportunities, along with geothermal features like hot springs.

name: Tsavo National Park
notes: One of the largest national parks in the world, known for its red elephants and diverse landscapes.

name: Nairobi National Park
notes: A unique park located just outside Nairobi, home to rhinos, lions, and giraffes, with the city skyline in the background.
